		<span class="time">February 06, 2014</span>
		<h2>HAMFERD to support AMORPHIS on east european leg in March 2014</h2>
	</div>
	
	<p>Faroese doom metal band Hamferd has been confirmed as the sole support act for Finnish melancholic dark metal masters Amorphis, whose second leg of the “Circle” world tour starts in the middle of march 2014.<br />
This is a unique bill for fans of dark metal music. Both bands are inspired by their Nordic traditions and surroundings. Amorphis draw huge inspiration from the Finnish national epic Kalevala and channel it through dark musical journey, whereas Hamferd shroud their Faroese folklore and doomladen hymns with a spellbinding uniqueness and mysticism. This is not the first time both bands are on the same bill. Hamferd had already done a support gig with Amorphis back in november in Hamburg, which was a great success. Hamferd guitarist Theodor Kapnas had the following to say about the upcoming tour:</p>
<p>“We&#8217;re really looking forward to hitting the road again! The clear highlight of our last European tour was opening for Amorphis in Hamburg, which was an incredible experience for us. So we&#8217;re delighted that we&#8217;ve been given the opportunity to open for Amorphis for an entire tour. Hope to see lots of people at the shows”.<br />
Hamferd will support on the European leg of the tour. The tour is presented by ROCK HARD, ZILLO, BLAST!, METALNEWS.DE.</p>
<p>The dates are the following:<br />
14.03. 	D 	Glauchau &#8211; Alte Spinnerei<br />
15.03. 	CZ 	Prague &#8211; Storm Club<br />
16.03. 	HU 	Budapest &#8211; Club 202<br />
18.03. 	BG 	Sofia &#8211; Mixtape 5 Club<br />
19.03. 	SRB 	Belgrade &#8211; Dom Omladine<br />
20.03.	HR 	Zagreb &#8211; Tvornica<br />
21.03. 	SK 	Bratislava &#8211; Majestic Music Club<br />
22.03. AT 	Graz &#8211; Explosiv<br />
23.03. DE 	Nürnberg &#8211; Hirsch<br />
25.03. CH 	Solothurn &#8211; Kulturfabrik Kofmehl<br />
26.03. DE 	Karlsruhe &#8211; Substage<br />
27.03. DE 	Hannover &#8211; Musikzentrum<br />
28.03. DE 	Düsseldorf &#8211; Zakk<br />
29.03. DE 	Lindau &#8211; Club Vaudeville<br />
30.03.	DE 	Aschaffenburg &#8211; Colos-Saal</p>
	
