	<div class="header">
		<span class="time">September 16, 2013</span>
		<h2>The Album of The Year -award!</h2>
	</div>
	
	<p>Amorphis received Metal Hammer´s &#8220;The Album of The Year&#8221; -award from the album &#8220;Circle&#8221;, released last April. </p>
<p>&#8220;For us, Album of the Year award is a great recognition for the work done so far. Especially when we got it from our 11th studioalbum. It is good to continue touring&#8221;, guitarist Esa Holopainen said.</p>
<p>Amorphis´s &#8220;Circle World Tour&#8221; will continue to Russia with 11 concerts. After Russia Amorphis will tour Australia and China for the first time. Check all Amorphis -gigs from <a href="http://amorphis.net/?page_id=5" title="HERE">HERE</a>.</p>
<p>&#8220;Circle&#8221; -album, released 19. April 2013, went straight to #1 on Finnish Official album chart and #1 on Rumba´s album chart. &#8220;Circle&#8221;´s positions on British Rock Album Chart (#15) and on German Album Chart (#13) are the band&#8217;s best so far in these countries. Amorphis was on Sweden´s album chart for the first time on their career. First week at #33. &#8220;Circle&#8221; was produced and mixed by Peter Tägtgren (Hypocrisy and Pain).</p>
	
